<dl id="s14037al"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us14" href="#s14037al">Oxen of the Sun: </a><a href="../../FF/unbs/s14all.htm#s14037al">sector 37(al)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> If &hellip; if . . the duke is guilty</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>If</mark> exact order, method, and true economy as a master of a family; <mark>if</mark> splendour and just magnificence, without wild waste and thoughtless extravagance, may constitute the character of an avaricious man, <mark>the Duke is guilty</mark>. <small> Anon, <a name="ALOJ" href="/udra/udex.htm#ALOJ"><cite title="source">Letters of Junius</cite></a> (1824), I, 174</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
